td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>&ge;100 mg/L (&ge;10 mg/dL)</p>\n</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*Comorbidities include chronic cardiac disease, chronic respiratory disease (excluding asthma), chronic renal disease (estimated glomerular filtration rate &le;30), mild to severe liver disease, dementia, chronic neurological conditions, connective tissue disease, diabetes mellitus (diet, tablet, or insulin controlled), HIV or AIDS, and malignancy.</p>",
        "facts": "<p>Interpretation:</p>\n<table width=\"311\" height=\"93\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>4C Mortality Score</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td><strong>Risk group</strong></td>\n<td><strong>In-hospital mortality</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>0-3</p>\n</td>\n<td>Low&nbsp;</td>\n<td>1.2-1.7%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>4-8</p>\n</td>\n<td>Intermediate</td>\n<td>9.1-9.9%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>9-14</p>\n</td>\n<td>High</td>\n<td>31.4-34.9%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>&ge;15</p>\n</td>\n<td>Very high</td>\n<td>61.5-66.2%</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
